author: State Journal staff
title: WIAA girls volleyball: Dodgeville wipes out a two-set deficit to beat Lodi in a regional opener
text:
1 of 2 WIAA GIRLS VOLLEYBALL WIAA girls volleyball: Dodgeville wipes out a two-set deficit to beat Lodi in a regional opener State Journal staff 0 
Junior Katie Valeria recorded 18 kills as sixth-seeded Dodgeville upset third-seeded host Lodi in five sets Tuesday night to open the WIAA Division 2 girls volleyball tournament. 
The Dodgers faced an early two-set deficit and were pushed to the limit before winning three consecutive sets to pull out a 22-25, 22-25, 25-18, 25-22, 20-18 victory. 
Junior Kara Crowley helped Dodgeville advance by contributing four blocks, five aces, and 19 assists. 
For Lodi, Kennedy Herbsleb recorded seven aces and 25 digs. 
Watertown Luther Prep 3, Lake Mills 1 
Alena Goba contributed six aces and 17 digs as the host Phoenix defeated the L-Cats 25-11, 23-25, 25-18, 25-9. 
Hannah Punzel recorded 15 kills and 17 digs to lead Lake Mills in the defeat. 
River Valley 3, Sauk Prairie 0 
Alyssa Mueller led the host Blackhawks with 26 assists in their 25-18, 25-21, 25-19 victory over the Eagles. Kelsey Reidel had 11 kills and three blocks for Sauk Prairie. 
McFarland 3, Marshall 1 
Emma Eckel, Katie Rounds, and Lexy Kemnitzer each had 11 kills as the host Spartans (28-12) overpowered the Cardinals (10-12) 24-26, 25-21, 25-13, 25-15. 
Bailey Neuberger recorded 13 kills and 14 digs to lead Marshall. 
Portage 3, Mauston 1 
The visiting Warriors defeated the Golden Eagles 27-25, 20-25, 25-19, 25-20. 
Senior Caitlin Hibner had 16 kills and 17 digs for Portage. 
Jefferson 3, Evansville 1 
Becka Cronin recorded 18 kills and 21 digs as the Eagles defeated the host Blue Devils 25-15, 14-25, 25-16, 25-19. 
Jaida Kroning and Samantha Kessenich each contributed three blocks in the Jefferson victory. 
Edgerton 3, Whitewater 0 
Ashlynn Oren recorded 13 kills and 19 digs to lead the host Crimson Tide over the Whippets 25-5, 25-18, 25-8 in a match between Rock Valley North teams. 
Bethany Oren contributed two aces and three blocks for Edgerton. 
Madison Edgewood 3, Columbus 0 
Kendra Lee had 10 kills and nine digs and Hannah Schwenn had 31 assists to help the host Crusaders sweep past the Cardinals. 
Schwenn also had nine digs for the Crusaders (23-13), and Meghan Conroy had a match-high four aces. 
Britta Hesselberg had seven assists and Kaylen Virgin had four kills for the Cardinals (5-15). 
Reedsburg 3, Adams-Friendship 0 
Bri Schyvinck recorded 10 kills and three blocks as the host Beavers (11-6) defeated the Green Devils (2-9) 25-12, 25-13, 25-9. 
Anna Pawlisch contributed four aces and three blocks in the Reedsburg victory. 
Richland Center 3, Mount Horeb 1 
The visiting Hornets picked up a 25-19, 23-25, 25-11, 25-19 victory over the Vikings. 
Walworth Big Foot 3, Monroe 0 
Sydney Mathiason contributed seven kills, but the Cheesemakers (0-9) fell to the host Chiefs (27-9-3) 25-11, 25-16, 25-17. 
Alicia Kuester provided three blocks for Monroe. 
DIVISION 3 
Mineral Point 3, Darlington 0 
The host Pointers defeated the Redbirds 25-20, 25-13, 25-18. 
Sydney Staver had 36 assists, six digs and two blocks to lead Mineral Point. The Pointers also got 15 kills from Clara Chambers. 
Cambridge 3, Beaver Dam Wayland 0 
Abby Spaanem contributed six aces and 11 kills as the host Blue Jays (6-10-0) overpowered the Big Red (1-15-1) 25-14, 25-16, 25-15. 
Regan Bolt also had three aces and 24 assists for Cambridge. 
Pardeeville 3, Winnebago Lutheran 1 
Kate Griepentrop had 14 kills and two aces as the host Bulldogs defeated the Vikings 23-25, 25-20, 25-21, 25-23. 
Madelyn Chapman contributed 28 assists for Pardeeville. 
Brodhead 3, Belleville 0 
The host Cardinals defeated the Wildcats 25-17, 25-16, 25-10. Abbey Johnson had 33 assists and seven aces for Brodhead. 
New Glarus 3, Orfordville Parkview 0 
The host Glarner Knights moved on to a regional semifinal with a 27-25, 25-17, 25-20 victory over the Vikings. 
Deerfield 3, Poynette 0 
The Demons advanced with a 25-18, 25-14, 25-10 victory over the visiting Pumas. Sheboygan sectional 
Lakeside Lutheran 3, Eastbrook Academy 0 
Kaitlyn Gehler had eight kills while Ellie Westrate had 13 assists as the host Warriors defeated Eastbrook Academy. Gehler also provided seven aces while Kendal Denson had eight digs for Lakeside Lutheran.
